msgid "**1. Hazards, Exposures and Impact**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/beginner/qgis-inasafe/212-understanding-inasafe.rst:32
# cb7e1e42d0164c43a164f5b6fa0dacdd
msgid "Let’s being by reviewing what we the inputs and outputs of InaSAFE - **hazard**, **exposure**, and **impact**.  These terms are important for you to remember because the analysis process will always depend on these three things."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/beginner/qgis-inasafe/212-understanding-inasafe.rst:36
# 4885dc8da3e84f80b5989a05b0f1748a
msgid "**Hazards** (also called disasters) are what we call the data layers (layers) that describe the extent and magnitude of natural events (such as earthquakes, tsunamis, volcanic eruptions) that could potentially cause an event or series of events that threaten and disrupt the lives and livelihoods of people."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/training/beginner/qgis-inasafe/212-understanding-inasafe.rst:41
# 803a9f2cc66146cb9c615463a99ecc63
msgid "Generally, hazards that we model:"
msgstr ""

